snippet: The Pakistani parents of a teenage girl were found guilty Friday of murdering her after she rebelled against their strict rules and a forced marriage to her cousin.
abstract: British court finds Pakistani parents Iftikhar and Farzana Ahmed guilty of murdering their teenage daughter after she rebelled against their strict rules and a forced marriage to her cousin; sentences both to life imprisonment.
lead_paragraph: The Pakistani parents of a teenage girl were found guilty Friday of murdering her after she rebelled against their strict rules and a forced marriage to her cousin.
